text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles. the accused have been booked for rioting, wrongful restraint and confinement, wrongly causing hurt, attempted murder, and sexual harassment.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text_retweet:
please repost or tag someone you think would be interested - the more people who see this, the better (link in profile):
"the national sexual assault online hotline, operated by @rainn, provides live, secure, anonymous crisis support to the growing number of people who prefer communicating online through a simple instant message format, giving those affected by sexual assault a safe place to receive support." as a new volunteer, i can say that receiving this training and working on the hotline has changed *my* life. not only am i able to make a difference for those in crisis, but it's boosted my knowledge and ability to this work in this space. and i'm as humbled by the experience as i am impressed by the expertise, dedication, and support from the people who lead this resource. the training gave me information and skills i could never have developed elsewhere, and they're applicable in so many areas of my life, not just when i'm actually working a shift. the training is extremely intensive, and the commitment (10 hours a month for 18 months) is realistic even in my busy life. 
i never thought i could do something like this - but the training changed everything. if you have questions, please feel free to ask. and even if it's not something you feel is right for you, please help me spread the word. ✒🖤
@thewordforthis

text_retweet:
repost:  @withrepost • @cheerupluv “i was coming home from one of my first ever club nights, and was walking out of the bus station when i felt the presence of a large group of men. i had never been so suddenly aware of my revealing outfit, and how inappropriate my shoes were. they surrounded me while shouting things at me that i still can’t even repeat to my own mother, and tried to grab me. i screamed at them through tears as i tried to break away from their circle. i can still hear their laughter ringing in my ears. i took my heels off and ran the whole way home trying to stave off a panic attack. i sat on the edge of my parents bed and cried and cried. i felt hopeless and embarrassed. 
it was the first time i really acknowledged what little ownership i had over my own body, and how little these men cared about my fear. it was even funny to them. i have never worn those heels out after that in case i have to run home again.” - bea 🌸
.
.
.
#cheerupluv #endsexualharassment #endviolenceagainstwomen #metoo #hearmetoo #london #timesup #itsabouttime

text: i didn’t sleep much last night due to pain and woke up in more pain than when i went to bed. this is my reality, so i decided to start my morning off with some unconventional feetup yoga in attempts to alleviate some of this ick. i find music to be so healing and soothing. in the background you will hear the most incredible song #figures by @jessiereyez it’s a very real and frank lyrical representation of domestic violence. if you find yourself in the unfortunate cycle of abuse, know that you deserve so much more. life doesn’t have to remain scary and painful. where there is a will, there is a way. i am not special in my ability to escape a tragic and dangerous life. i won’t pretend it’s easy and that the unknown is not scary. but ask yourself this, “can you attach a price tag to freedom?” i am answering that for all of you out there suffering.......no! @mcleanataylor @themntnman @jennipeeps @tsylvester6 #domesticviolence #domesticviolencesurvivor #childabuse #parentalalienation #metoo #metoomovement #woman #womanempowerment #backbone #risen #freedom #loveyourself #grateful

text:
a shout out to single moms. i am a “statistic”. i was raised by single mom. i am a single mom. we are bad ass mo-fuk’n women. 
this year, i’ve been working hard at “accepting” my “situation” (so it’s been called), including changing the language to “this is #myfamily ”. this is the hardest job i’ve ever had in my life. i didn’t plan on raising a family by myself. i spent my fair share of days crying, or feeling guilty for not feeling enough. i’ve felt ashamed to tell people my truth about my family. i’ve had men who are coupled up specifically stay away from because they don’t want their wives to think i’m hitting on them. i’ve had people not wanting to get together with me and my kids because i don’t have someone to entertain their husband (a significant other). i’ve been afraid to tell potential employers in the past that i am a single parent, concerned they would evaluate me based off of my personal life. i’ve had people ask me “what does your husband do”, and have just lied because i don’t want to be reminded that day that i am alone. 
in 2018, i made a choice to be alone, and to walk away from an abusive relationship. i am thankful everyday for the people who helped me do this- it was hard. my biggest insecurity of being a single parent is what kept me there for so long, hence why i am paying homage to the single parents of this world whether it was a choice, or not. 
being a mom with a partner can already be a lonely job. being a single mom is even lonelier. so cheers to the fucking single moms/dads who get up every day and feed your kids, and cheers to the single moms/dads who take their kids to the park or anywhere else really, and cheers to single moms/dads who can place their life issues aside and still give their kids the time of their lives, and cheers to this fucking stigma because it just isn’t relevant anymore! 
thank you to everyone who has accepted us, for us and who are helping me raise these fantastic boys of mine. i’m so fortunate to have been handed such loving humans to call my own who grab life by the balls/ovaries and just giv’r 
#singlemom #singleparent #ittakesavillage #momofboys #carryon #metoo

text:
on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

reposted from @world -  pope francis has publicly acknowledged for the first time that there is a problem of priests and even bishops sexually abusing nuns in the roman catholic church. after he was asked to comment on the issue during a news conference aboard a plane returning to rome from a trip to the united arab emirates, the pope admitted that the issue is ongoing and said that they must do more to fight the problem. in recent years, catholic nuns in india, africa, latin america, and italy have accused clerics of sexual abuse, and a vatican magazine last week mentioned nuns having abortions or giving birth to the children of priests, according to the new york times. (📹: reuters)

text:
as a survivor of sexual assault, my healing comes in waves. there are months where i feel strong and empowered - where i want to take on the world and show my grit and determination to thrive, despite the evil that has existed in my world. but then the months come where i am drained, exhausted, and filled with self hatred. in these dark times, healing seems distant. i feel an overwhelming sense of unworthiness. that no one could ever love the broken parts of me. that it’s all for naught. i do not feel strong. i do not feel brave. and finding the will to even exist becomes my greatest struggle. and these thoughts consume me, day in and day out. and it hurts. and it makes me angry.

however, on my journey to self love - i decided to tape this to my bathroom mirror a few months ago so that i am reminded daily that i must be compassionate toward myself. i deserve love, peace and rest, joy, and so much more. if i do not give myself these things - then my abuser wins. and i no longer can give him that kind of power over my life. 🌻🌻🌻 won’t you join me, my sisters, in this journey of radical self love and acceptance? •

name: Speaking Truth Together
tweet_full:
as a survivor of sexual assault, my healing comes in waves. there are months where i feel strong and empowered - where i want to take on the world and show my grit and determination to thrive, despite the evil that has existed in my world. but then the months come where i am drained, exhausted, and filled with self hatred. in these dark times, healing seems distant. i feel an overwhelming sense of unworthiness. that no one could ever love the broken parts of me. that it’s all for naught. i do not feel strong. i do not feel brave. and finding the will to even exist becomes my greatest struggle. and these thoughts consume me, day in and day out. and it hurts. and it makes me angry.

however, on my journey to self love - i decided to tape this to my bathroom mirror a few months ago so that i am reminded daily that i must be compassionate toward myself. i deserve love, peace and rest, joy, and so much more. if i do not give myself these things - then my abuser wins. and i no longer can give him that kind of power over my life. 🌻🌻🌻 won’t you join me, my sisters, in this journey of radical self love and acceptance? •

•
•

text:
#walkwithwambui 
i struggled with internalized victim-blaming
•
 in many ways i had been my own biggest enemy when it came to victim- blaming. for a long period i treated myself badly...every passing day it felt that it was my fault it happened to me😞
to some point i knew it wasn't my fault but i still couldn't stop doing it........ victim blaming!!! a great number of victims and survivors are struggling with internalized victim-blaming which leads to one hating themselves to an extent of committing suicide.
today society is constantly telling us that us who have been sexually assaulted are to blame, but the truth is when it comes to abuse the only person to blame is the person who chose to abuse.  so let's stop victim blaming!! #endvictimblaming

text:
sgbv training on 9/2/2019 (sat) 
our heartfelt thanks to organizers (mewro), melisa and team from women aid organization (wao) malaysia, hui ying tham the director of asylum access malaysia, cherryn certe (co-ordinator, mewro) secretary of fro sponsored for lunch and refreshment, the place is accommodated by malaysia karen organization,  the participants, ruth education center (rec) , kachin refugee committee, alliance of chin refugees, chin refugees committee,  arakan refugee relief committee,  zomi refugee committe,  zomi associations of malaysia, mon refugee organization, shan refugee organization, dai community, malaysia karen organization.

we believe empower women is empower society. to break the chain of violence,  we need to educate our society.

participants feedbacks 
from today’s’ lesson called “sgbv” i discovered that it is not the fault of those who dress up very uncomfortably when they go out or anywhere but it is the fault of those who look at them insecurely. yet, it doesn’t mean we are allowed to wear whatever we want, we should be aware and that we should dress up comfortably and securely. and another thing i was reminded is that women and man are equal ; the characters and qualities are almost all the same. therefore, women too have the same right as man.
from jenny:. i learned much from this training. one lesson is about how to help in a crisis. the people who help out in those 
situations are called pfa which stands for psychological first aid ( first thing that happens after an accident(. pfa can be done by anyone.
let's say,  unfortunately there is an earthquake. from that fact the survivors will need help in terms of physical (eg.food,water etc.), mental & emotional (fear, worried ect.), social & economic ( house,land ect.) in order to help the people the pfa needs to have good communication.
there are three steps look, listen, link. firstly, look-we need to be calm & 
show understanding, our body languague & eye contact are

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
just play nice.
be nice.
try to be nice.
play nice at school.
speak nicely.
be nice in that meeting.
make sure you’re nice about it.

who do we say these words to? 👧🏽girls. 👩🏻‍🦰women.
🧑🏼ladies. 👱🏿‍♀️females.

not boys. not male colleagues. not husbands. not male bosses. not any male.

you know what? it’s ok to not be nice sometimes. it’s ok to lose your temper, have a rant, shout, get frustrated and be anything but nice. you are human, not a fairytale fantasy of a meek mild perfectly manicured woman.

#feminist #equality #selflove #positivevibes #feminism #empoweringwomen #empowerment #metoo #nice #women #ladies #girlpower #quotes #rights #society #selflove #confidence

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
after @iamreginaking won a golden globe award this month for her role in the film, if beale street could talk, she made a vow in her acceptance speech to equally represent women in everything she produces.

one of the justifications for not hiring women, is the lack of access. regina says one way to overcome this is to work with organizations, like women in media, who encourage gender balance in the industry by providing women with access to networking, professional development, and advocacy. “i've seen a couple articles that say i’m not being realistic. on our set now both of our camera teams have women on them. it's not impossible. it's just not being done. so, i'm going to show you.” over on @forbes , regina shares her plans and advice for how women can support other women. link in bio to read ⬆️
.
.
.

text:
watch the trailer for new #metoo film ‘rocking the couch’
#
one of the most important releases of the year, rocking the couch, available on demand this february from avail films.hollywood titans, harvey weinstein and bill cosby, have been brought to their knees by the #metoo movement. but they did not invent casting couch. the term casting couch has existed for decades. but in 1992, a case against talent agent, wallace kaye, was brought to court by 12 unknown actresses, who braved the loss of their careers, their privacy, and their hollywood dreams. they stepped forward, despite the advice of their union, and brought the case to the police. against all odds, they won, and no one listened.our documentary explores the case and asks, "why didn't we hear about this?" more importantly, why didn't hollywood learn from this case? for, if they had, maybe the cosbys and the weinsteins would have learned as well, and these sexual exploitations could have been prevented."those who ignore history are bound to repeat it."from writer/director minh collins, produced by andrea evans, minh collins, and jerry sommer, and starring lauren anastasi-peter, ikon barenbolm, alana crow, jennifer durst, andrea evans, tiffani fest and sadie katz, rocking the couch is now available on amazon u.s and uk. watch…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/watch-the-trailer-for-new-metoo-film-rocking-the-couch/

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i have been following anti-flag and seeing them as much as i can on their tours since 2014, and i am always appreciative of every new album, every new song, and every show they play. i am so lucky to have been able to see them in three countries, on two different continents, for one amazing experience. the first time i saw anti-flag was at amnesia rock fest in 2014, and i absolutely knew then and there it wouldn’t be the last.
⠀
i just want to say thank you to @justinsane for giving me the voice i thought i lost. 
your strength, resilience, and compassion has touched so many people, and i am so thankful for you. ⠀
⠀
@chrisnumber2, thank you for continuing to support and advocate for change is so many avenues, especially for the benefit of victims of violent crimes. your #metoo support has helped more than you’d ever know. thank you for being kind, thoughtful, and determined despite any crossroads that you have met.
thank you both for being such incredible role models ❤️
⠀
thank you to @godofthunder666 for always being kind and compassionate. your energy radiates through the venues every time i see you play. congrats on the baby (: ⠀
⠀
and thank you to @xchrisheadx for being so kind at eden cafe and being one of my favourite guitarists for so many years. i am so glad to come back and you’re still as awesome as the show before 💓💓
⠀
thank you for everything @antiflag
name: lauren 🐟
tweet_full:
i have been following anti-flag and seeing them as much as i can on their tours since 2014, and i am always appreciative of every new album, every new song, and every show they play. i am so lucky to have been able to see them in three countries, on two different continents, for one amazing experience. the first time i saw anti-flag was at amnesia rock fest in 2014, and i absolutely knew then and there it wouldn’t be the last.
⠀
i just want to say thank you to @justinsane for giving me the voice i thought i lost. 
your strength, resilience, and compassion has touched so many people, and i am so thankful for you. ⠀
⠀
@chrisnumber2, thank you for continuing to support and advocate for change is so many avenues, especially for the benefit of victims of violent crimes. your #metoo support has helped more than you’d ever know. thank you for being kind, thoughtful, and determined despite any crossroads that you have met.
thank you both for being such incredible role models ❤️
⠀
thank you to @godofthunder666 for always being kind and compassionate. your energy radiates through the venues every time i see you play. congrats on the baby (: ⠀
⠀
and thank you to @xchrisheadx for being so kind at eden cafe and being one of my favourite guitarists for so many years. i am so glad to come back and you’re still as awesome as the show before 💓💓
⠀
thank you for everything @antiflag

text: ¿estáis dispuestos a renunciar a vuestros privilegios por un mundo más igualitario? el machismo se cura leyendo y escuchando. la reconstrucción no solo es necesaria en los hombres, también en las mujeres. si las feministas estamos dispuestas a aceptar que nos hemos criado en el heteropatriarcado y que debemos reeducarnos para un mundo más justo, leyendo y escuchando a otras mujeres. ¿por qué hay tantos hombres negados a hacerlo? nosotras abrimos nuestros brazos a cualquier sexo siempre que tenga la mente abierta para aprender lo que es realmente el feminismo.

text:
shout out to my dear sister friend marcia pendelton of walk tall girl productions for the chance to check out "the light" by loy a. webb at mcc theater. bravo to @mandimasden and @mckinleybcubed who deliver stunning performances while unpacking the complexities of black love --- and masculinity and femininity ...in these polarizing times of #metoo, #timesup,  #muterkelly,  and #kavanaugh. you must see the light by loy a. webb. directed by logan vaughn. now thru march 17 at mcc theater, 511 w. 52nd street, nyc. tickets $45/$75 with code mccwtgp (reg $69/$99) for tickets and more info visit www.mcctheater.org #lifeofriley 
p.s. hill harper and carl nelson were in the house!
p.p.s. look for more on the light with an upcoming d. briggs media look at nyc theater 2019.

text: after listening to @goldiehawn’s desert island discs for the second time, i’m embracing my inner gh. i’m utterly inspired by all the work she’s done with mind up, and that she refuses to hide any part of her fabulous self. my latest piece on balance garden talks about embracing the authentic you. it’s scary to allow yourself to be seen from all sides, so today i’m saying screw you to that and wearing the red dress whilst working on some social change promoting, education giving and art making projects. 💪🏼

text:
when tarana burke started #metoo, who would have thought it will arrive in india and how!

but ever since the movement broke out, there’s been a slew of commentary on ‘what the movement sets out to do’. while some have come out and extended massive support to the women who are finally mustering courage to speak against those men in power who made life and work a trauma, some have left us aghast at their (no)pologies or comments.
.
.

p.s. hill harper and carl nelson were in the house!
p.p.s. look for more on the light with an upcoming d. briggs media look at nyc theater 2019.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
yesterday was a funny day for emotion

saying goodbye to one life... being surrounded by the people you love the most.

reminiscing over the good times full of love and laughter... knowing you should make time for more...
_
i sat there last night thinking how many times we live inside the life of others, not going after what we want

not living our most authentic selfs because it doesn’t fit with the people we are choosing to spend our lives with...
_
or the job we are choosing to stay in...
_
or with the friends we don’t quite fit with.

when did you decide your happiness didn’t matter?

when did you decide you weren’t worth putting first?

time to ask yourself what you really want...
_
and go after that! take the risk!

life is too short not fill it with laughter and happiness ❤️

text:
“i’m 15 years old and i’m a victim of sexual assault.” those words pierced my heart. a teenage girl uttered them just seconds after a male teenager announced he came out to his parents.  i honestly didn’t know how to react until i heard the thunderous applause from everyone around me at the fiorello h. laguardia high school 2019 rising stars this is me: a journey talent show. 
it takes courage to stand in front of a group of strangers and make these admissions, i thought. 
i’d come to the show at the urging of my mentee, emily. i didn’t feel like going by the time 6 o’clock rolled around. yet, i said good night to the writer i’d been training for half the week and headed to dinner with emily.

after we caught up, we fought the wind coming off the hudson river on manhattan’s upper west side to make it back to her school just in time for the start of the show.

there were familiar tunes like, “beautiful” “my funny valentine,” “unpretty,” “huddled masses” and “out here on my own.” but, the original song “the outspoken truth,” spoke me. it boldly outlined injustices and inequality in our society while celebrating uniqueness, bravery and strength. it helped me see that we should all use our talents to entertain, as well as share our truth, hopes and aspirations without shame, fear of rejection, judgement, and persecution. 
#talent #mentoring #spoonies #autoimmunedisease #invisibleillness #chronicillness #chronicpain #blogger #writinglife #highschool #laguardiahighschool #loveconquersall #metoo

text:
film d’ouverture du scarlett cinéma club ✨🎬
.
[revenge, 2018] .
aujourd’hui j’ai fait le choix d’introduire notre ciné-club par un premier long métrage de la réalisatrice française coralie fargeat. le film se rapproche d’un rape & revenge, un style cinématographique souvent traité par des réalisateurs hommes dans un genre horrifique. très controversé, c’est un genre de cinéma volent et faisant polémique à raison, du voyeurisme malsain au male gaze déplacé. je trouve néanmoins interressant de vous présenter #revenge sorti en 2018 qui met en scène l’actrice matilda lutz et dont le regard féministe de coralie fargeat qui excelle dans la réalisation donne un nouveau souffle et une réapropriation du genre à l’ére de #metoo. le film n’est pas très réaliste, parfois grossier s’inspirant presque des nanars américains mais l’énergie pop, les décors désertiques à la mad max et l’adrénaline offerte à la pelle font de ce film un petit bijou de cinéma indépendant. j’ai hâte d’en discuter avec vous et de connaître votre avis sur ce film. on annonce la couleur du ciné-club et elle commence par le rouge sang, symbole du massacre de la masculinité toxique. . [tw] ce film contient des scènes violentes, du sang (beaucoup) et une scène de viol.

text:
your abusive partner doesn’t have a problem with his anger; he has a problem with your anger.one of the basic human rights he takes away from you is the right to be angry with him. no matter how badly he treats you, he believes that your voice shouldn’t rise and your blood shouldn’t boil. the privilege of rage is reserved for him alone. when your anger does jump out of you—as will happen to any abused woman from time to time—he is likely to try to jam it back down your throat as quickly as he can. then he uses your anger against you to prove what an irrational person you are. abuse can make you feel straitjacketed. you may develop physical or emotional reactions to swallowing your anger, such as depression, nightmares, emotional numbing, or eating and sleeping problems, which your partner may use as an excuse to belittle you further or make you feel crazy. .
.
.

text:
#рассказыоживотных
#рассказыокошках
#кошкамоя
#кошкаэтосчастье
#кошкавдомеэтосчастье
как коту предлагали дружбу 😼

соседского жиробасика баксика все достало, и он решил податься в бега в рио-де-жанейро. и начал с подъезда: выскочил на площадку, пометался по лестнице и затих за мусоропроводом. сидит и понимает, что нифига это не рио-де-жанейро, и похоже, что он не подумал. а мимо люди ходят – злые, равнодушные, страшные. что делать? проблема. 
и тут мимо идет соседка анжелика, баксик ее хотя бы пару раз, но видел – уже почитай родная. он выскочил, упал на колени и взмолился: «не бросай, мол, на растерзание, помоги домой вернуться!». она поохала, поизумлялась и начала звонить хозяйке баксика. а той дома нет и на телефон она не отвечает – сама, поди, свалила в рио. 
видя неподдельный ужас в глазах баксика, анжелика вздохнула и потащила его домой, где уже проживали муж и кот вася с гаремом из кошек аси, ветки и рони. против был только муж, но его удалось успокоить, что это временно и вечером баксик вернется домой. остальные разбрелись по квартире, не выказав никакого интереса к новенькому. 
веселуха началась ночью. соседка по-прежнему не отвечала на телефон, и баксику было предложено поесть и лечь спать на кухне. первый пункт он исполнил, а со вторым вышла проблема. к вечеру женсостав квартиры рассмотрел новоприбывшего принца: молодого, красивого, толстого, с огромными янтарными глазами и красным носом. шикарная плюшевая шерсть, мощные лапы и круглые полосатые бока … в общем, стерилизованные дамы посовещались и пошли предложить баксику дружбу. 
уже уснувшая было анжелика подлетела от диких криков. баксик-мученик отчаянно орал под столом, что это харрасмент и он будет судиться. кошки переглянулись, удивились и пошли знакомиться сомкнутым строем. баксик взвыл от ужаса, кот вася закрыл его собой и был затоптан – баксик взлетел на шторы и выл оттуда: «#metoo». анжелика уговаривала его целый час, тянула за шторы, успокаивала. кошки разводили руками и говорили: «ничего ж не сделали, только вошли…». баксик рыдал и просился домой, никакой рио-де-жанейро больше его не интересовал. 👇

и тут мимо идет соседка анжелика, баксик ее хотя бы пару раз, но видел – уже почитай родная. он выскочил, упал на колени и взмолился: «не бросай, мол, на растерзание, помоги домой вернуться!». она поохала, поизумлялась и начала звонить хозяйке баксика. а той дома нет и на телефон она не отвечает – сама, поди, свалила в рио. 
видя неподдельный ужас в глазах баксика, анжелика вздохнула и потащила его домой, где уже проживали муж и кот вася с гаремом из кошек аси, ветки и рони. против был только муж, но его удалось успокоить, что это временно и вечером баксик вернется домой. остальные разбрелись по квартире, не выказав никакого интереса к новенькому. 
веселуха началась ночью. соседка по-прежнему не отвечала на телефон, и баксику было предложено поесть и лечь спать на кухне. первый пункт он исполнил, а со вторым вышла проблема. к вечеру женсостав квартиры рассмотрел новоприбывшего принца: молодого, красивого, толстого, с огромными янтарными глазами и красным носом. шикарная плюшевая шерсть, мощные лапы и круглые полосатые бока … в общем, стерилизованные дамы посовещались и пошли предложить баксику дружбу. 
уже уснувшая было анжелика подлетела от диких криков. баксик-мученик отчаянно орал под столом, что это харрасмент и он будет судиться. кошки переглянулись, удивились и пошли знакомиться сомкнутым строем. баксик взвыл от ужаса, кот вася закрыл его собой и был затоптан – баксик взлетел на шторы и выл оттуда: « анжелика уговаривала его целый час, тянула за шторы, успокаивала. кошки разводили руками и говорили: «ничего ж не сделали, только вошли…». баксик рыдал и просился домой, никакой рио-де-жанейро больше его не интересовал. 👇

the event last month in the uk house of commons, sponsored by jldh, brought together campaigners for the prevention of sexual violence and parliamentarians into a discussion on what steps need to be taken to end it for good.
nadia murad, nobel peace prize winner 2018, said: “as someone who has come to understand the importance of advancing and defending human rights, i am proud to be a voice for all victims of sexual violence in conflict. the lai dai han have been living in the shadows of vietnamese society for far too long. the victims and their families deserve to be recognised as we work together to achieve justice.”
.

text:
sekste rıza kavramının çay metaforu üzerinden anlatımı...
.
kadına yönelik şiddet, taciz ve tecavüzün eksik olmadığı türkiye’de ‘rıza mefhumu’, şule çetdavası, klinik psikolog murat paker’in danışanına ‘cinsel saldırıda’ bulunduğu suçlamasıyla 4 yıl 2 ay hapis cezasına çarptırılması ve #metoo hareketinin akademiye sıçraması gibi güncel örneklerle birlikte yeniden gündeme geldi.
.
eğer hala anlamakta zorluk çekiyorsan, biriyle seks yapmaya çalıştığını değil, ona çay hazırladığını düşün. “çay ister misin?” diyorsun ve sana “tabi ki! harika olur! teşekkür ederim!” diyorsa bil ki gerçekten çay içmek istiyor. “ya aslında emin değilim…” derse, ona çay hazırlayabilirsin ama aklında olsun, içmeyebilir ve eğer içmezse (burası önemli) ona çay içirmeye çalışma. düşük bir çay içme ihtimali var diye çay yapma zahmetine girmiş olduğun için onu suçlayamazsın. çay içmek istemediğini kabul etmek zorundasın. çayı yapmış olman onu mutlaka o çayı içerken izleme hakkın olduğu anlamına gelmez. “hayır, teşekkür ederim” derse, çay yapma. o kadar. çay yapma, ona içirme, içmek istemedi diye kızma. anla işte çay istemiyor.

sana, “evet, teşekkür ederim” deyip, çay geldiğinde aslında istemediğini söyleyebilir. evet, onca zahmete girdikten sonra bunu duymak seni gıcık edebilir. ama hala hiçbir şekilde çay içmek zorunda değil. önce istiyordu, şimdi istemiyor. bazen insanlar sen çayı yapmaya başladıktan çay hazır olana kadar geçen sürede kararlarını değiştirebilirler. bunda bir sakınca yok. bu yine de sana çayı zorla içirme hakkı vermez.

bilinci yerinde değilse, çay yapma. bilinci yerinde olmayan insanlar “çay ister misin?” sorusunu anlayamazlar.

text: the biggest story rn in politics. things aren’t looking good for virginia, first the governors pics w him in black face leaked and then this.... some ofthe democrats are calling for his resignation but he didn’t even go through a trial yet. the thing is that he’s a democrat so all democrats should be rallying against him if they all would rally against a republican that would do the same thing. do we believe the man or the (2) women? what is the fairest way for us as a society to handle something like this? it seems like in a situation like this the public and the media have more power than the judicial system. and i’m curious to know when that shift happened. i mean the clarence thomas case definitely helped insert the media into the narrative but anita hill got a lot of backlash. after #metoo launched, the media were heavily inserted again. so maybe once harvey weinstein’s sexual assault cases piled together and the media kept covering it, the women of #metoo did some really great pr with getting everyone on every talk show across the country, led by rose mcgowan.

#wino #miód #wine #honey
wino gronowe 🍷  i miód pszczeli 🍯 to jedne z najstarszych naturalnych produktów spożywczych towarzyszących rozwojowi ludzkości. nie może zatem obok regałów przedniego wina zabraknąć pszczelich produktów. bartnictwo 🐝 na podkarpaciu ma bardzo daleko sięgające tradycje. dobre warunki naturalne sprawiają, podkarpackie miody cieszą się wspaniałą opinią, a niektóre ich odmiany wpisane są na listę produktów tradycyjnych mrirw. dlatego na naszych półkach zagościły różne odmiany miodów 🍯🍯🍯 z pogórza przemyskiego, z gospodarstwa pasiecznego m. jurczyszyna ze śliwnicy (nieopodal krasiczyna, gdzie na zamku urodził się arcybiskup krakowski, kardynał adam stefan sapieha). zapraszamy na kielich wina i po pszczeli eliksir na retoryka 21. 😋

text_retweet:
#repost with @repostlyapp @earthlove777 rp @meat_your_future 
the miracle of life is torture for dairy cows, as their babies are taken from them again and again.
.
like any mammal, cows only produce milk for their calves, after they delivered a baby calf. but because we want their milk, we forcibly impregnate them over and over, to get and keep them lactating, and take their calves away after they are born.  this obviously causes intense distress for both the mother and her baby.
.
the surplus calves (including all of the males who will never produce milk) are "discarded" (killed) as “byproducts” of the dairy industry.
.
the female calves who are not killed will become the next generation of milk producers themselves. like their mothers, they will be impregnated over and over, just to have her babies taken from her as well.
.
so the mother’s heartbreak and stress of losing her baby will be repeated over and over again, until her milk production declines, at a fraction of her natural lifespan, at which time she will be sent to a violent and terrifying slaughter.
.
humans have not consumed milk past weaning or from a different species for the majority of our evolution. we absolutely do not need it for our health, we don’t need it for our bones, and indeed we are much healthier avoiding it completely.
.
and, of course, there are plant-based versions of every single “dairy” product you can think of (non-dairy milks, ice creams, cheeses, etc.).
.
please recognize the serious consequences of your food choices, and the suffering it inflicts on sentient animals. please go vegan and ditch dairy foods (and all other animal products) forever.
.

text:
🦋 #metoo 
schroef je lieveling..... the brave and compassionate tarana burke, an activist from harlem, launched the movement a decade ago to aid underprivileged women of color affected by sexual abuse. 
she was inspired after bonding with a young girl during a youth camp hosted by just be inc., a nonprofit she founded that’s “focused on the health, well-being, and wholeness of young women of color,” the site reads. 
the two-word phrase resurfaced in october 2 years ago when actress alyssa milano took to twitter to invite those who have experienced sexual harrassment to respond with “me too.” her tweet followed the new york times’ oct. 5 investigation into decades of sexual harassment allegations against hollywood producer harvey weinstein, and within hours #metoo went viral on twitter, facebook, instagram and beyond as people took to the platforms to share their personal accounts of sexual assault. 
i wrote my first non fiction book five years ago “sex in the suburbs.” a true story. i made a promise to study mental health, counsel women, write my empowerment books, give motivational talks, work with women’s refuges, my local government, travel the world inspiring women to a new brighter beautiful future! everything i could think of to empower women. 
i can happily say it’s working! 
big things are brewing! 
it’s been ten years since i manifested my vision of the life i desired and now i’m having it!! stay tuned.... i am here for anyone who wants a little magic in their lives, a spell or two, and universal spiritual understanding. 
namaste ~leeza~ 🖤🦅 #wildchild #passion #spirit #love #metoo #counsellor #healer #writer #book #speedo #film #actor #streetphotography #model #inspire #igdaily #millionaremindset #dream #whitewitch #wicca #spell #millionairelifestyle #luxury #jetset #jetsetter #travel #explore #fitness #healthy #manifest @modelredress @wheelsanddolbabes

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

text:
monica potter claims resisting harvey weinstein seduction barred her from ‘cider house rules’ role
##metoo #breaking news #casting #commentary #controversial #harassment #harvey weinstein #media #monica potter
actress monica potter claims that she lost a chance to appear in the 1999 film the cider house rules because she rejected harvey weinstein’s advances. speaking to her hometown cleveland television station wkyc on its let’s be clear show, potter said weinstein had tried to bed her three times, “twice in new york and once was in london.” on two occasions, weinstein made advances while wearing a bathrobe, she claimed. she rejected him physically, she said, taking advantage of his attire. “i belted him. i flat out belted him… i really hit him where it hurt,’ she exclaimed. ‘so yeah, i missed out on that role because of that hairy pig.” she added: “i didn’t do something, so therefore i missed out on it. i’m not saying the person who got it did. i’m just saying i didn’t.” the cider house rules lead female role of candy kendall was played by charlize theron in the film. potter claimed she told her father about the first weinstein incident, but did not talk about the others until her confession today. potter said she was “so grateful for all the women that stood up” against weinstein and revealed similar confrontations. weinstein’s representative told wkyc in a statement that the allegations were false, even though weinstein had great respect for the actress. “the final cast decisions on cider house was the creative team’s alone. close to 100 people auditioned and it came down to two people, which is a pretty good position to be in,’ the representative’s statement said. “there has never been anything other than respect and professionalism between weinstein’s company and ms. potter, stemming from the very thought of you in 1998, and they have only had a friendly and cordial relationship over the years, and any suggestion or allegation otherwise is simply false.”

text:
uplift each other 💜

ruu pks harus segera disahkan demi keselamatan dan keadilan bagi semua korban kekerasan seksual (baik perempuan maupun lelaki)

for me, this is non-negotiable. movement #metoo dan advokasi untuk segera sahkan ruu pks masuk dalam payung yang sama, seeking justice | keadilan. 
kita harus berhenti “making excuses” untuk predator seksual, kita harus berhenti victim blaming, kita harus berpihak pada korban, and damn right kita butuh sistem hukum yang akan menjanjikan keadilan bagi korban, dan accountability untuk pelaku kekerasan seksual. 
let’s keep lifting each other up, not pushing each other down 💜

illustration by @thaaks.i previously posted by @muslimgirl

every one of my releases so far has been close to my heart, but my upcoming ep ‘no evil’ includes one of the most important songs i’ve ever written. the song, ‘talk’, is a little about my experience(s) with sexual abuse and about the subject in general. i felt like it would be appropriate to post this before the release to make anyone who might need to be aware of the subject matter aware before listening to the song. it is a subject i believe needs to be talked about more in order for healing to happen and for people to be educated on the matter. this song and the video that will come with it is my contribution to the conversation.

text:
woody allen contro amazon e amazon contro trump.
[reading time: 50 secondi] 
amazon studios è stato accusato di aver violato il contratto stipulato con il regista woody allen su quattro film, tra cui l’ultima creazione “rainy day in new york”, senza alcuna spiegazione lecita.
le uniche giustificazioni utilizzate dal gigante amazon contro il regista risalgono al 1990, periodo in cui woody era stato accusato di molestie dalla figlia adottiva dylan farrow, notizia recentemente riapparsa grazie all’hashtag #metoo, movimento femminista che tratta della violenza sulle donne, specialmente nel settore cinematografico.
i problemi nel rapporto tra #amazon e #allen hanno iniziato a farsi sentire dal 2017, a seguito delle dimissioni dell’ex presidente degli #amazonstudios, roy prince, sotto accusa anch’egli per molestie, facendo così slittare l’uscita del nuovo film di #woody “rainy day in new york”, dal 2018 al 2019 a causa del passato del regista che avrebbe potuto impattare negativamente sulla produzione amazon. 
i 68 milioni di dollari che allen chiede sono per la mancanza di giustificazioni valide che, nello scorso giugno, hanno portato alla cessazione del contratto da parte del colosso, mandando in fumo tutto il lavoro e la carriera del regista, in cerca tuttora di un nuovo distributore cinematografico. 
nel frattempo, jeff bezos è coinvolto a sua volta contro l’editore e sostenitore di trump per scandalo mediatico: il “national enquirer” avrebbe infatti  minacciato e successivamente ricattato tramite e-mail il proprietario di amazon con foto in cui appare nudo insieme a lauren sanchez, giornalista televisiva. 
per #bezos appare inevitabile collegare questo scandalo a #trump, che da sempre lo considera un proprio rivale, “come appare ovvio dai suoi tweet” afferma jeff. 
pensate che queste notizie possano avere impatti negativi su amazon ? come potrebbe reagire il mercato dopo queste accuse? 
#diccilatua nei commenti

text:
30 children. pure innocence came to play on thursday. from the minute they arrived magic would unfold.

one terrified little boy quivered with fear. i suggested he hug the tree he stood in front of. nature heals. and our secret enchanted garden is filled with healing.

30 children went on a journey of discovery. they wowed throughout the experience. too much magic no one ever said.

their life stories are heart breaking. they suffer in silence. until one day, as an adult, i get that email, the whatsapp. pleas for help. a story of millions of women across our city, country and continent. and the world too.

they tell me their stories. they suffer in silence. they won't write books. they have never heard of the #metoo movement. i cannot be their saviour or their comfort. i can create magic. we all need magic & miracles in our lives.

i have so much abundance in my hands. they told me to use them to heal. the golden gift. i never understood. still working it out. the gold gift box awaits delivery. it's now, or never. what's the best that can happen?

olde worlde counter of yesteryear counting modern world magic 🦄

text:
pope francis has publicly acknowledged for the first time that there is a problem of priests and even bishops sexually abusing nuns in the roman catholic church. after he was asked to comment on the issue during a news conference aboard a plane returning to rome from a trip to the united arab emirates, the pope admitted that the issue is ongoing and said that they must do more to fight the problem. in recent years, catholic nuns in india, africa, latin america, and italy have accused clerics of sexual abuse, and a vatican magazine last week mentioned nuns having abortions or giving birth to the children of priests, according to the new york times. (📹: reuters)

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
can we enrich masculinity? 
to where men aren’t judged and labelled as weaklings for wearing their hearts on their sleeves
 to where young boys don’t have to develop unhealthy coping mechanisms just because society has taught them this is what it takes to be man enough. 
to where there is less domestic violence, and more loving homes.
to where women and children don’t have to deal with unnecessary trauma.
to where men are brave enough to stand up for women and their rights.
to where promises aren’t for fooling.
to where women don’t succumb to sexual harassment just to keep their jobs.
to where emotions, which are a god-given charm, do not impose any danger to masculinity, nor the definition of strength.
to where there are insightful social norms and constructs.
redefining masculinity is nowhere equal to omitting it. 
now can we? 
embrace humanity, compassion and empathy

notice 1: this article does not, in any way, disclaim any abhorrent and despicable acts done by women.

notice 2: this is a message of warmth, you do not have to suffer alone; according to statistics, suicide is more prevalent in men.

before criticising, please ask yourself “why not?”. art by: @klaudiapavlicko

to where women and children don’t have to deal with unnecessary trauma.
to where men are brave enough to stand up for women and their rights.
to where promises aren’t for fooling.
to where women don’t succumb to sexual harassment just to keep their jobs.
to where emotions, which are a god-given charm, do not impose any danger to masculinity, nor the definition of strength.
to where there are insightful social norms and constructs.
redefining masculinity is nowhere equal to omitting it. 
now can we? 
embrace humanity, compassion and empathy

notice 1: this article does not, in any way, disclaim any abhorrent and despicable acts done by women.

notice 2: this is a message of warmth, you do not have to suffer alone; according to statistics, suicide is more prevalent in men.

before criticising, please ask yourself “why not?”. art by: @klaudiapavlicko

text:
meanwhile in poland 🇵🇱 .

this is so surreal guys.  i can’t begin to tell you how awesome it is to be in a foreign country and meeting teams in your organization from
every corner of poland. almost all of them i’m meeting for the first time!! .

i can’t believe this all started because i said yes to living my life on my own terms.  check out the next slides to see two amazing women who are locking arms together and making their dreams come true for them and their families. .

i always knew that there was more to life then just earning an income. that i wanted a chance to make a difference in this world.  i didn’t know how. i just put it out into the universe. 
keep reading if you want to know what that looked like. ⬇️⬇️⬇️ .

thats when the opportunity presented itself in the form of my own business that had no limits. something i could build from home and have a piece of the international digital market world. .

i was all in and now...... .

there’s  incredible momentum in @martagierczynska organization and i can feel a nation coming!! before the end if the year. i’m calling it.  just watch!! .

i’ll do my best to post pics and give you and insiders look at her car show which is completely sold out.  over 180 guest are traveling from all corners of poland to be here!! many have already showed up and checked into the hotel a day early. .

this is really going to be a dream come true for all of us.  you can’t keep the smile from @kingakorta ‘s face.  it feels like a wedding.  wait till you see marta’s dress tomorrow!!! .

pinch me!!! one decision really does have a ripple effect.  are you ready to build your dreams instead of getting paid to build someone else’s.  we should talk.

text:
this week on @popcultureconfidential: ‘r kelly/bryan singer/michael jackson/weinstein, shocking exposés and survivors getting heard!’ i am joined by rachel leah writer at salon.com covering culture, race and criminal justice.

we talk about the shocking wave of articles, exposés and documentaries about allegations of sexual misconduct by high profile artists and industry titans. allegations that have dogged them for years, sometimes even for decades. how can it be possible that these allegations have been industry, and even public, knowledge for years and still their careers flourish? but has the #metoo movement allowed for more survivors to come forward with their stories when the justice system seems to often have failed them?  rachel leah has been covering these topics extensively and joins us this week for an in-depth conversation.

words for the world:
me too part 9.
a series. .
.
.
passion and violence
i want to feel alive
so much so
i have a death wish. .
.
.
i know not to 
trust you
yet you know how 
to trigger each 
of my fears.
i feel controlled 
by you - it thrills me
you might kill me 
if i try to get away. 
i know
i might do it anyway
if i feel alone again. 
and each and every
morning it is the same
you force your way 
on top of me
telling me i want it,
but i know you 
get off by them hearing,
you love to
disgrace me, 
so its even worse.
no one wants 
a used up whore. -mahriyah willow

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
отношение общества к женскому телу совсем не такое, как к мужскому. женщинам надо быть прежде всего красивыми, радовать глаз. и соответствовать классическим стандартам красоты: низкий вес, тонкая талия, большая грудь, отсутствие волос на теле и т. д. собственное восприятие красивого для женщины не приемлимо. общество хочет контролировать женское тело и женскую сексуальность: нельзя носить короткую юбку, слишком глубокое декольте, нельзя размещать фотографии своего тела в социальных сетях. тогда как мужчины таким запретам не подвергаются. у общества также есть система запугивания для женщин, которые нарушают запреты: пугают изнасилованием на улице, увольнением с работы, оскорблениями в адрес женщины. 
о чем вообще может идти речь, если некоторые до сих пор спрашивают у парня, можно ли им выложить ту или иную фотографию.
патриархальное общество полностью контролирует социальную и личную жизнь женщины, она всегда находится под пристальным вниманием мужчин, боясь их осуждения.
но вы им ничего не должны, вы не обязаны объяснять свои поступки, свои волосы на теле, свой гардероб и любые свои предпочтения. живите так, как хотите вы.
#феминизм #bodypositive #feminism #metoo #photoshop #photo #art #polaroid

discussing the #yogasutras in our #yogateachertraining seems to get more interesting every year. 
the concept of #bramacharya (“chastity” in the more conservative readings, “integrity in sexual relationships” in the liberal ones) is always...a topic of strong interest for people. 
most especially now, in the wake of #metoo , i can’t get through the lecture without wanting to scream: “sex is not the problem! it’s not even the issue!” because, in the world and time we’re living in, sex is not the issue. the unspoken abuse of power is the issue. 
in my experience, the healthiest perspectives on sexuality do not come from clergy (#duh) or from philosophers. they come from those whose experience of sexuality has been commingled with marginalization or violence—and who have as a result *insisted* on something better. 
so i can’t give this lecture without thinking of the beautiful souls who lived and died in the depths of the aids crisis, who gave us the tools to stay healthy through their own dogged, our-lives-depend-on-this research—when our government was happy to just let folks die. 
i can’t give this lecture without thinking of the leather community, who forged a way to talk about power dynamics and sexuality with consciousness and consent at the forefront. 
i can’t talk about this stuff without also thinking of the horrendous effects that sesta/fosta has had on sex workers, and how state-approved violence has always been leveled as a threat against any woman who dared to assume her body belonged to her alone. 
it’s a lot. but #philosophy is only meaningful when it’s #alive.

there's about a 6 year difference between these two pictures. i've always (and i mean always) struggles with my weight. i was always the bigger girl, the fat girl. i was bullied all through school. i became depressed and suicidal. it didn't matter how hard i was working towards my goal, it was never enough for  everyone around me. i would try and stay as active as possible, but get discouraged every time i'd have someone watching me. i always felt like i was never enough, or i would never be good enough for anyone. i hit a rough patch in my life. i stumbled into an abusive relationship (mentally, physically and emotionally). i was raped. i lost a ton of weight in a short period of time. but i wasn't happy. i lost the weight due to the situations that happened. once that relationship ended i gained a lot of it back. that was 5 years ago. in the last year i got more active, got my life back on track, started caring more about my mental health and doing what's right for me. i'm finally in a happy place, and excited to start this journey again, with a happy and healthy mind.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: hey! the following is a rant. so if aren’t interested in reading what an educated, pissed off woman thinks about the grammies, about the music industry, or about the #metoo movement, you’re welcome to look at my abs in this picture or to just leave this post entirely. i actually did a lot of sit-ups. and “no”, i really don’t think i’m “all that.” don’t worry. | there are very good reasons that women’s voices are missing from popular music, from stages, and from screens. and it’s because we have been systematically silenced and excluded. a lot of people asked why i stopped performing. and it’s because one psycho ruined it for me. i don’t feel safe performing. cyber stalking often leads to real life stalking. and you know what? being stalked isn’t fun. you can block a psycho on every social media, on your phone, on your email...and if he knows enough about you and is a little tech savvy, he’ll find a way to keep bothering you. this piece of shit even harassed my mom. i hope he rots in hell. my experience isn’t unique. it’s common. and it drives a lot of women to take more powerful roles as creators, in business and art. there will be a day when men like the piece of shit that has made my life a living hell will think a few more times before fucking with a woman. i wrote a lot of angry songs for a while.  and i really am glad that i did. it gave me the courage to move beyond my rage and into a place of health and wellness. no one will ever fuck with me again. that’s for sure. i can sell that kind of dirtbag twenty miles away. ladies, let me know if you need any help identifying the stench of a goodfornothing. #metoo #fuckoff also, i’ve put on a solid 10 pounds of muscle since then and have learned to a) punch b) kick above my head. whatever. i’m feeling like a boss today. and i don’t mind sharing it, just in case you need a reminder that you’re a boss too, queens. #feminism #newyear #fitfam
name: Yasmine Van Wilt, PhD FRSA
