•• h e a l i n g •• through the arts of survivors and allies #advocate #idaho ———————————————————————— as part of sexual assault awareness month, the family crisis center is seeking creative projects for the april 2019 “ healing – through the arts of survivors and allies”
we want to hear about any original work that will contribute to the message of the exhibit. photographers, painters, sculptors, choreographers, writers, graphic designers, curators – all creative disciplines are encouraged to apply.
entries close on friday, march 29. for anyone wishing to submit their piece, please contact julie at juliel@familycrisiscenter.info with “april 2019 exhibit” as the subject.

text:
🌺 we welcome presenter tania loveheart, to the 2019 retreat - tania is deeply inspired by life to hold space for others to offer people opportunities for self-development and self-empowerment. it has been through her own learnings as life that she believes unwaveringly in the power of self-affirming thought, belief and action that moves mountains and parts the seas.
✨
her discussion workshop at is about creative expression : honouring the freedom of emotional expression. ✨
tania says …”i believe each and every one of us is called at some point of recognition to honour the self in light of emotional freedom.
✨
as a human being, you have the capacity to express yourself through the gift of emotional sense. for many, however, these emotional senses are a hindrance to their wellbeing. we've been taught to suppress our emotions and hence they become underdeveloped. ✨
opening up to the wonder and the freedom to express emotionally not only develops your capacity to unburden emotional suffering but also allows the self the freedom to live life fully in honour of the self.”
🌺 
you are most welcome to join our tribe of beautiful women at the 2019 boundless self love retreat :: invoking the warrior woman, where we will be creating a circle of connectivity helps eliminate isolation. at this retreat you will experience empowering workshops and activities, meet awesome people and have to to feel, be heard and be fully seen. absolute soul food!
✨
early bird tickets available for a limited time! ✨
🖤 see more event and ticket info in our bio link 🖤
✨
red tent australia is a kind, caring, supporting, national, non-profit, social enterprise.
✨
our regular #retreats offer #yoga #meditation #palm readings #reflexology #tarot #aromatherapy facials #remedial massage #sound chime relaxation #reiki #bonfire #dancing. ✨
our next retreat is on saturday 25th – sunday 26th may 2019 :: you are warmly welcome to join us. tickets will sell out, see link for more info or to book, in our profile bio.
🌺
#womensretreats  #healingretreats #invokingthewarriorwoman2019 #boundlessselfloveretreat #acceptance #belonging #community #womenscircles #bslr2019 #redtentau  #metoo  #goddess  #support

text:
1.
yesterday i posted a #tbt; today is #fbf. both are from the same photoshoot, which took place during a time when i was at an emotional rock bottom. when i look at the photos from this pinup shoot, i see a confident woman, comfortable in her body…. but that’s not accurate. .
.
the reality is that at the time these photos were taken, i was obsessively counting calories and struggling to work off everything i ate during the day, and at night i was making midnight bodega runs and eating until i physically couldn’t eat anymore – essentially, cutting, only with food – before throwing it all up… and the next day, doing it all over again. my bingeing and purging was out 👏 of 👏 control. i had put on 30 lbs in 6 weeks. .
.
cont’d. in comments ➡️

text:
por qué woody allen no tiene quién estrene su nueva  pelicula.

este 2019 no tendremos película de allen para ver, por más que a rainy day in new york la haya terminado hace mucho.

no sólo los argentinos; nadie en todo el mundo la podrá ver, porque amazon, que produjo la película, decidió no estrenarla.

y woody allen, tras un largo silencio desde junio del año pasado, decidió demandar al gigante del entretenimiento por algo de dinero.

son 68 los millones de dólares que pide. ¿se acuerdan cuando querían traerlo a dirigir una película a la argentina, por 15 millones de dólares? “amazon ha intentado justificar su acción haciendo referencia a una acusación sin fundamento de hace 25 años en contra de allen, pero esa acusación ya era bien conocida por amazon, antes de que amazon alcanzara cuatro acuerdos con allen”, se lee en la demanda presentada por los abogados de allen, de 83 años, recogida por variety.

para los que lo olvidaron, mia farrow, que era su esposa, por 1992 alegó en medio del proceso de separación que allen había abusado de dylan, a quien habían adoptado juntos.

parece que mientras se estrenaba la rueda de la maravilla en nuestro país, y en plena eclosión del movimiento #metoo en contra del acoso sexual, fue amazon quien le propuso al realizador esperar y retrasar el estreno de su nuevo filme.

text_retweet:
repost from @bitchmedia - ✨adventures in feministory: fannie lou hamer ✨⠀
.⠀
fannie lou hamer, like many women activists of the american civil rights movement, is often overlooked despite her staggering contributions to social change. ⠀
.⠀
in 1962, hamer attended a meeting of the student nonviolent coordinating committee (sncc), and instantly became interested in civil rights, specifically voting rights. numerous challenges were set up to keep black people from voting in mississippi, including written tests and poll taxes. she immediately made efforts to register to vote and of course immediately faced police brutality, racist harassment, and unemployment. hamer eventually did register to vote, and also became a sncc field secretary.⠀
.⠀
fannie lou hamer was a founding member of mississippi freedom democratic party, which was formed to challenge the all-white, anti-civil rights mississippi democratic delegation sent to the 1964 national convention. in addition to this, hamer also began a day-care center in her hometown of ruleville, was part of the delta ministry, a community-organizing and support network, raised money for low-income housing, was on the board of a garment plant designed for more jobs, and even ran for u.s. congress in 1965 with two other women.⠀
.⠀
✨adventures in feministory is a series highlighting the important and often overlooked contributions of women throughout history. in honor of #blackhistorymonth, we are spotlighting black women who have made waves, enacted social change, and left a lasting impact for future generations to come. ✨
.
image design by @neonhoney 🎨
.
.
.
.
.

from how we met to signs god sent to seeing you carry out what you have to, a man on a mission and meeting everyone in between. i’m proud of you and what have you after your film came out brother. btw i’m still craving that malta lmao. if y’all haven’t watched “amani” go youtube it right now and watch it and share it. i’ve done watched it over a dozen times already and gotta say big ups to all the actors, your direction and seeing your vision pan out. aside from that seeing you now venture out and even doing knife wars, i’m glad to have met someone like you bro and call you family cause you’re an inspiration. and everyone else in this video @romaylewade @livelikewass and my mentor @mgisme164 everyone had a role in everything. love bro i can’t wait to see the opportunities god has laid out for all of us including all the actors in the film big ups to @kingellisw  and @joivan_wade i swear uk actors are hands down super talented. lmao i guess u can say this is an homage to everything you’ve done and my trip to london while i was there. love and blessings 🙏❤️❤️
.
.
.

text:
this is parent alienation and co-parent alienation. step parents matter in children’s lives. we are just as important and held to an even higher standard than their own parents. i was the one that was strangled. she almost ended my life with her hands. it is frightening to witness a complete deflection and redirection on her playing the victim in this equation. it’s as if she were jealous of the attention that i was getting from her daughter because i was hurt so she faked a pregnancy and then says that she lost the baby only to find out that she has started menopause?!!!! maybe that’s why she attacked me? i don’t know. stab me in the eye with a pencil please because that would hurt less than the agony that this woman has put us through physically, mentally and emotionally. i do not appreciate the scattering of her shat all over my life at least bring a poop bag of you are going to come to my home and act like an animal. and that is me very upset. scary? scale 1-10? go.

text:
let’s support!!!! @brandy_3232 granddaughter. https://dm2.gofund.me/11-month-old-brain-trauma.m  syren maloney or sy-sy was born on february 5th, 2018. an incident with a hired caregiver  on january 30th, has now put her into a fight for her life. this unfortunate incident resulted in trauma to sy’s brain, liver, spleen, and her ribs. she has had a procedure that has removed a portion of her skull and is on a ventilator along with various medications. syren has had many ups and downs since her admission, but she is resilient and strong with god and your prayers.

sy’s family has traveled from all over the country to be with her during these critical times in her healing process. syren’s first birthday will be in the hospital, but there will be many more celebrated outside of it. we will keep the faith that she will see many more birthdays. 
this account was created to aide syren with her medical expenses. 
we appreciate your support, prayers, and positivity in this challenging time. please share this page with your family, friends, coworkers, church members, classmates, etc.

this account is managed by syren’s mother, necol, and father, kee. 100% of the proceeds from this gofundme will go to assisting syren’s recovery. thank you and god bless.  #childabuse #abuse  #cptsd #mentalhealth #abusesurvivor #anxiety #trauma #metoo #domesticviolence #children #recovery #survivor #childabusesurvivor #emotionalabuse #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #recoveryisworthit #childabuseawareness #panicattack #recoveryishard #realrecovery #love#help#

text: what a wonderful and empowering day this has been for me! getting to listen to these strong, powerful, resilient, and passionate women leader’s (the list can go on and on) today has been one of the greatest learning experiences for me. understanding that being my authentic self will generate success, how to discover and utilize my strengths to accomplish my goals, discussing equal rights for all women, grasping the concept of intersectionality, and understanding the downfalls of white feminism are only some of the key points i took away from the conference. all of the keynote speakers and panelist were so excellent! like melissa abad, ph.d. who is a sociologist at the stanford vmware women’s leadership innovation lab and leads the women intersectional leadership research agenda. or @monica.stockhausen who became a professor at the age of only 24 and now owns her own company nerdy girls rock! which is designed to professionally develop ie women in the collegiate and professional market. and finally the presidents of the national women’s march @tamikadmallory @bobblandofficial! not gonna lie i fan-girl’d when i saw tamika mallory! i mean cmon a woman who worked closely with the obama admin. as an advocate for civil rights issues?! or bob bland speaking about the #metoo movement and opening my eyes to understanding my attack mattered and i am not to blame regardless of circumstances. and i should not be ashamed or afraid to tell my story. these women are definitely role models and people i look up too. so it was an honor getting to be here today and learn from these amazing women! looking forward to the next women’s leadership conference! ❤️💪 thank you #csusb! #csusbwomensleadershipconference #activatetomotivate #womensleadership #tamikamallory #bobbland #survivor #inspire #motivate #empower #womensupportingwomen

text:
day 5, awareness week. unfortunately this is how i met @missangeline00. just randomly following each other on instagram i came across her post from the hospital letting everyone know she was ok. i almost didn't reach out. i was afraid she would think i was insane. but she hopped right on board with the idea.

this photo had to stay unreleased until now for reasons beyond our control. until now. this is bravery, this is strength. this is a model who stepped back in front of a camera less than a week after getting beat up by her (ex)boyfriend to say "this shit needs to stop now!" who's with us?

text:
hosting my second galentine’s of the month and had to make this fruit cookie pizza because it was such a hit so i had to share it with y’all! i subbed the lemon juice with a few drops lemon oil and everyone couldn’t get enough! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
ingredients:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
crust:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1/4 cup butter, softened
1/2 cup sugar
1 egg
1/2 tsp. vanilla
1 1/4 cups flour
1/4 tsp. baking powder
1/4 tsp. baking soda
1/4 tsp. salt
filling:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4 oz. cream cheese, softened
1/4 cup powdered sugar
1 cup whipped topping (i used cool whip)
fruit topping:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i used raspberries, blueberries, and blackberries, but you can use whatever types of fruit you like.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
glaze:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1/4 cup sugar
2 tsp. cornstarch
1/4 cup water
1/8 cup lemon juice
for crust: cream butter and sugar together. add in egg and vanilla, mix. add flour baking powder, baking soda, and salt, mix. press dough into heart shape onto a greased cookie sheet. bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. cool completely.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
for glaze: mix sugar, cornstarch, water, and lemon juice in a small saucepan. bring to a boil over medium heat and then boil for a couple of minutes until thickened. cool for about 30 minutes.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
for filling: beat cream cheese and powdered sugar. add whipped topping and mix well.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
now put it all together! spread filling onto cookie crust. add your desired fruit. then drizzle the glaze over the top. store finished valentine fruit pizza in the refrigerator.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

tweet_full:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subve elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
95.5% of prisoners in the uk are men. men are more likely than women to be arrested by police for doing the same crime. men are more likely to be prosecuted by the cps than women for doing the same crime. men are more likely to be given a jail sentence by the courts than women for doing the same crime. men are more likely to serve a longer sentence with the prison service than women for doing the same crime.... so the bbc runs 3 articles about female prisoners!

partially the discrimination against men is subconscious, given that women are always portrayed to be the victim, and partially it's by design. here's a female green party leader saying it is right for women to be punished less for the same crime because punishing women affects their families... the insinuation being that punishing men doesn't break up families. punishment should be based on the crime, not what gender, race, or anything else the person was born!

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
two more weeks before i end chapter 12 of book 39 in my life story. much has come my way over the last year that may have been meant to break me. but, here i am unbroken and joy filled. this last year has also brought a lot of wonderful times and happy memories. and, so again i say here i am unbroken and joyfilled.
i am happy, because i choose to be happy within myself first.
i am loved, because i choose to love myself first before expecting someone else to. 
not everyone who pretends to care really does, and that is ok. not everyone, who claims they'd be there for me was, and that's ok. not everyone who says they miss me when i run into them ever checked on me, and that's ok. not everyone is honest, and that's ok. 
i have distanced myself from a lot of people, because my mental well-being is important. i've decided i don't want to start my next book off celebrating with people who have not been genuinely there for me. so, no celebrations with a lot of people. i will celebrate with those i choose and prefer no one attempts to choose for me. it's my choice, and i truly hope people can and will respect my decision.

text:
hannah gadsby has a thing or two to say about picasso
pen and ink and watercolor pencil on bristol 
11 x 14
part of the misunderstood women series 
just don't miss hannah gadsby's 'nanette' on netflix.  i'm not sure it's correct to call it comedy. i do think it's an important social document. and it's funny.  and it's heartbreaking. 
she talks about what i began to suspect when i saw the picasso sculpture exhibition at moma and noticed all the sculpted  women had clenched fists.  then there's the painting of the woman with a fish on her head.  the editor of the book i read thought maybe it was a commentary on the scarcity of food during the war. i imagine rather that perhaps the model complained about her hat so he punished her by putting a fish on her head.

hannah was the easiest to draw in this series so far; she's a very clear communicator. .
.

.
.

text:
do klaus nomi and julie andrews come to you in dreams?
.
.
++++++++
.
.
it's 1981. 
kling klang!
julie and klaus went to a kraftwerk concert in provence, taking in "the hall of mirrors" and "franz schubert" and what have you. they sat afterwards at the dark bar next door, drinking tamarind whiskey sours, and talking about sketchy humans, harassment, abuse of power and smear campaigns. they talked about groupthink, post-apocalyptic tribalism, and their shared love of campy film “the warriors” and soothsayer philip k. dick’s novel “do androids dream of electric sheep?” and fear as the great motivator for detrimental behavior. "me too," sighed julie, "for monsters walk among us.”
.
.

julie and klaus left the bar to meet up at the late-night recording session of their friend nick’s band, where they were wrapping up final tracks for a self-titled debut album called “duran duran.” the guys let julie and klaus record for a bit into the wee hours of the morning, with the guys adding some synth and guitar layers.  when they were all done recording this new song “playful memory,” and the sun was peeking through the dingy window on the east end of the recording studio, john taylor put his feet up and laced his fingers together behind his head and mused, “like kraftwerk says, ‘even the greatest stars dislike themselves in the looking glass.’” and they all had a good laugh.
.
++++++++++++
.
.
the real "playful memory" single (by me) is being mixed by wizard lee wiggins as we speak, and will be launched in all the internet places one launches independent music these days in a free society. i hope you come out to playayyyyyyyyy.
.
+++++++++++
.
.

text:
________________________________________человек спросил у жизни: - почему я так живу? скучно, неинтересно…

и жизнь ответила ему: - потому что жизнь проходит мимо тебя. ты - словно «премудрый пескарь» - спрятался от нее. а жить нужно так, чтобы жизнь из любопытства остановилась, не прошла мимо, заинтересовалась. и осталась … тогда ты будешь счастлив._____________________________и вдруг наступает мгновение, и ты понимаешь, нет - ощущаешь, что
жизнь проходит... как будто заглядываешь в черную дыру, в бесконечную пустоту...
и не пробуй задавать умных вопросов! ответов нет уже давно. и надо жить на свете просто, 
пока нам жить еще дано. любовь дарить своим любимым... друзьям - поддержку в трудный час... и постараться быть такими, чтоб люди понимали нас...
... и все-таки с улыбкой говорю, что эта жизнь проходит не напрасно. и в новый день врываясь, как на праздник, я сам себе удачу подарю... (из инета)

жизнь проходит... как будто заглядываешь в черную дыру, в бесконечную пустоту...
и не пробуй задавать умных вопросов! ответов нет уже давно. и надо жить на свете просто, 
пока нам жить еще дано. любовь дарить своим любимым... друзьям - поддержку в трудный час... и постараться быть такими, чтоб люди понимали нас...
... и все-таки с улыбкой говорю, что эта жизнь проходит не напрасно. и в новый день врываясь, как на праздник, я сам себе удачу подарю... (из инета) 
   sychological_hрelp

text_retweet:
for your knowledge 
reposted from @harrieteve9 -  richmond, virginia — the political crisis in virginia exploded wednesday when the state's attorney general confessed to putting on blackface in the 1980s and a woman went public with detailed allegations of sexual assault against the lieutenant governor. with gov. ralph northam's career already hanging by a thread over a racist photo in his 1984 medical school yearbook, the day's developments threatened to take down all three of virginia's top elected officials, all of them democrats.

the twin developments began with attorney general mark herring issuing a statement saying he wore brown makeup and a wig in 1980 to look like a rapper during a party as a 19-year-old student at the university of virginia. herring — who has been among those calling on northam to resign — said he was "deeply, deeply sorry for the pain that i cause with this revelation." he said that in the days ahead, "honest conversations and discussions will make it clear whether i can or should continue to serve as attorney general." then, within hours, vanessa tyson, the woman whose sexual assault allegations against lt. gov. justin fairfax governor surfaced earlier this week, issued a detailed statement saying fairfax forced her to perform oral sex on him in 2004 during the democratic national convention in boston.

tyson, a 42-year-old political scientist who is on a fellowship at stanford university and specializes in the political discourse of sexual assault, said, "i have no political motive. i am a proud democrat." "mr. fairfax has tried to brand me as a liar to a national audience, in service to his political ambitions, and has threatened litigation," she said. "given his false assertions, i'm compelled to make clear what happened." the associated press typically does not identify those who say they were sexually assaulted, but tyson issued the statement in her name. fairfax — who is in line to become governor if northam resigns — has repeatedly denied her allegations, saying that the encounter was consensual and that he is the victim of a strategically timed political smear. {swipe◀️} source: ap
#metoo #virginia

whether hater or supporter, contributor or reporter, you are jttots. 
thank you for coming to my ted talk.

text:
check out my most recent article (link in bio) for the good, the bad, and a real solution to the backlash
--
from recent @bloomberg and @nytimes articles, to tiffany dufu's @tdufu @msnbc interview (shared earlier this week and available @dralessandrawall), to an email i just received from my sons' school - subject title: "raising kids in the #metoo era" - it looks like the #metoo movement continues to gain traction, and that's a good thing... or is it?⠀
--⠀
on the one hand, it's heartening to see we're still talking about harassment, appropriate behavior and the importance of speaking up even when you feel all alone; movements like these tend to come and go like shoe trends.⠀
--⠀
on the other hand, an all too predictable reactive backlash doesn't bode well for male-female relationships in the workplace.⠀
--⠀
read the full article: "trust in the workplace in the #metoo era" via the link up top (@dralessandrawall). let me know your thoughts in the comments: is the #metoo movement a good thing?⠀

text:
“i don’t know about ghosts,” she was saying; “but i do know that our souls can be made to go outside our bodies when we are alive. ... a very easy way to feel ‘em go is to lie on the grass at night and look straight up at some big bright star; and by fixing your mind upon it, you will soon find that you are hundreds and hundreds o’ miles away from your body, which you don’t even seem to want at all.”
-tess
•
before my husband and i officially started dating, we picked out favorite books for each other to read. i made my yet-to-be boyfriend read this book, tess of the d’urbervilles, which in retrospect was an interesting choice to give a boy i really liked, because the major theme of this whole book is basically that men suck. i guess he didn’t read too much into it, because obviously things worked out between us (i mean, i found a guy who was willing to read classic lit for fun and could talk to me about intelligently, clearly i fell head over heels for him. also clearly, he’s way better than angel clare.)
•
i just reread this again for my virtual book club, and what an interesting read in the era of #metoo. hardy was a feminist before feminism was a thing.
•
normally, i don’t go in for super depressing books (which is why i pretty much hate modern literary fiction), but for some reason, i love tess with all my heart. maybe i see a lot of myself in her (her personality, not her experience thank goodness). whatever it is, i highly recommend this book. despite the tragic beginning, despite the tragic ending, despite the fact all the men are terrible, it is a beautiful read.
•

text:
international women's day falls on march 8 - this is a friday. for most in the hospitality industry, it's a tough day to commit – it's the busiest day/night of the week. .
.
this year, minibar canada will be hosting a series of events. our annual seminar series will move to mon. march 4th.
.
women’s awareness week vancouver will include:
.
mon. march 4, 2019 – the well beings sessions, 9:30 a.m. – 3:00 p.m.
tues. – fri. march 5 – 8 2019 – celebrate the city 
sat. & sun. march 9 & 10 – weekend rituals .
.
all details and tickets will be released on feb. 18 2019. please mark your calendars for this, and the schedule of events outlined here. space is limited and all events sell out quickly. #minibarcanada #balanceforbetter #iwd2019

text:
international women’s day falls on march 8 - this is a friday. for most in the hospitality industry, it’s a tough day to commit – it’s the busiest day/night of the week. .
.
this year, minibar canada will be hosting a series of events. our annual seminar series will move to mon. march 4th.
.
women’s awareness week vancouver will include:
.
mon. march 4, 2019 – the well beings sessions, 9:30 a.m. – 3:00 p.m.
tues. – fri. march 5 – 8 2019 – celebrate the city 
sat. & sun. march 9 & 10 – weekend rituals .
.
all details and tickets will be released on feb. 18 2019. please mark your calendars for this, and our schedule of events outlined here. space is limited and all events sell out quickly. #minibarcanada #balanceforbetter #iwd2019

text:
rp @meat_your_future 
the miracle of life is torture for dairy cows, as their babies are taken from them again and again.
.
like any mammal, cows only produce milk for their calves, after they delivered a baby calf. but because we want their milk, we forcibly impregnate them over and over, to get and keep them lactating, and take their calves away after they are born.  this obviously causes intense distress for both the mother and her baby.
.
the surplus calves (including all of the males who will never produce milk) are "discarded" (killed) as “byproducts” of the dairy industry.
.
the female calves who are not killed will become the next generation of milk producers themselves. like their mothers, they will be impregnated over and over, just to have her babies taken from her as well.
.
so the mother’s heartbreak and stress of losing her baby will be repeated over and over again, until her milk production declines, at a fraction of her natural lifespan, at which time she will be sent to a violent and terrifying slaughter.
.
humans have not consumed milk past weaning or from a different species for the majority of our evolution. we absolutely do not need it for our health, we don’t need it for our bones, and indeed we are much healthier avoiding it completely.
.
and, of course, there are plant-based versions of every single “dairy” product you can think of (non-dairy milks, ice creams, cheeses, etc.).
.
please recognize the serious consequences of your food choices, and the suffering it inflicts on sentient animals. please go vegan and ditch dairy foods (and all other animal products) forever.
.

text:
i gave a talk at @makerswomen yesterday about financial literacy and what comes after #timesup and #metoo for us. for me its #ialso
years ago when i started down this path i did not understand what a #fuckyounumber was. a fuck you number is a term that i was introduced to by my guy friends. it is a number past retirement, that entitles you to only do the things you chose. 
every guy i know can tell me his #fuckyou number but women become paralyzed with this question. we as women need to get beyond networking and get into "net worthing". when i was younger, good lawyers, wealth managers, bankers and investors were limited and i did not understand all the dynamics of capital, liquidation preferences, strike prices, cap tables, options, and complicated deal structures. 
men know these things because they talk about it. making money is a function of friendship for men but its not for women. that has to change. 
every day women get hazed  not because we are getting inducted into, but for simply wanting to be in the paid club. 
making money is an essential part of equality and we need to get focused on that. while we have benefited from a pr halo in a post #metoo and #timesup world, it has yet to create a wealth movement for us. 
so for me after #metoo and #timesup its #ialso
i also want generational wealth, investments and opportunity
i also want the opportunity to fail and try again
i also want to be shame free, entitled to my place in the world as the leader i want to be. #ialso link in bio 🧵@tiffthestylist

text:
rörelsen #metoo fick sitt stora genombrott år 2017. det var den amerikanska skådespelaren alyssa milano som uppmanade andra skådespelare att berätta om deras egna erfarenheter gällande sexuella trakasserier, övergrepp och våldtäkter. sådana sexuella ofredanden visade sig vanliga, men hade hittills tystats ner. den 8:e november 2017 i ett gemensamt upprop i svenska dagbladet samlades 703 skådespelar och berättade om sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier som de bevittnat eller utsatts för i film- och teaterbranschen. #tystnadtagning startades av några kvinnliga skådespelare och det fick enormt genombrott både i sverige, utomlands och inom sociala medier. efter det följde en lång rad uppror från andra branscher.

gemensamt för ”landsföreningen för kvinnans politiska rösträtt” (lkpr) och me-too rörelsen i sverige var/är synliggörandet av den patriarkala präglade samhällsstrukturen. de kvinnliga skådespelare och alla de andra kvinnor som under me-too rörelsen höjde sina röster utan att skämmas, bli dumförklarade eller nedtystade gjorde precis samma sak som de kvinnor som kämpade och höjde sina röster under tidigt 1900- tal för att inte ännu en gång bli nedtystade av män.

⁣

text:
part 3 on my exhibition from china with love at @hugomichellgallery by @sophiatron :
a key part of just’s artistic practice is an engagement with broader communities through socially inclusive interventions. the fabric scroll me too 我也是 rice bunny 米兔 was made in response to the me too movement and in recognition of the individual stories of women in china. the title is an allusion to the hashtag #metoo, which was censored on social media in china. in its place, netizens and feminists of china used the words 米兔(rice bunny), which phonetically sounds like ‘mi tu,’ to address sexual harassment and discrimination. the fabric piece is embroidered by more than sixty women just met and invited to participate, with their individual narratives literally being stitched together to tell a bigger story. the resulting work is a powerful testament to feminist solidarity.
photo 1: @samrophoto 
photo 2: @katejustknits 
photo 3&4: @simonjstrong

a key pa of just’s aistic practice is an engagement with broader communities through socially inclusive interventions. the fabric scroll me too 我也是 rice bunny 米兔 was made in response to the me too movement and in recognition of the individual stories of women in china. the title is an allusion to the hashtag  which was censored on social media in china. in its place, netizens and feminists of china used the words 米兔(rice bunny), which phonetically sounds like ‘mi tu,’ to address sexual harassment and discrimination. the fabric piece is embroidered by more than sixty women just met and invited to paicipate, with their individual narratives literally being stitched together to tell a bigger story. the resulting work is a powerful testament to feminist solidarity.

text:
tarana burke has worked tirlessly to raise awareness of sexual violence and assault in our society. she began the #metoo movement in 2006 and gained national recognition in 2017 after victims of sexual harassment began to share their stories. ⁣
⁣
her campaign began to promote empowerment through empathy among women of color who had experienced sexual abuse. ⁣
⁣
today we celebrate and honor tarana burke. ⁣
⁣
#blackherstory #taranaburke #bhm #blackhistorymonth #opbsi⁣

on this episode we have caitlin currin, who joins us to share her personal story of transformation from being consumed in a chaotic, abusive, and destructive relationship - escaping and ultimately finding healing and love within herself and with a new partner.
a word of caution: on this episode we explore sensitive and traumatic experiences involving domestic violence. though we encourage all to listen, please do so at your own discretion.
 this episode is sponsored by the national coalition against domestic violence. their mission is to be the voice of victims and survivors of domestic violence. they do this through affecting public policy, increasing understanding of the impact of domestic violence and providing program and education that drive change. if you would look to support these causes please click the link below to learn more about how you can be a part of the change. also, if you or anyone you know is being abused, please dial the domestic violence hotline at 1-800-799-7233.
national coalition against domestic violence: ncadv.org

text:
breaking news
.
.
.
a second woman has come forward accusing virginia lieutenant governor justin fairfax of sexual assault.

in a letter from her lawyer, meredith watson claims she was raped by fairfax in 2000, when they were both students at duke university. 
the letter characterizes the alleged attack as “premeditated and aggressive.” the two were friends but never dated or had any romantic relationship,” the letter says. “ms. watson shared her account of the rape with friends in a series of emails and facebook messages that are now in our possession,” the letter continues. “additionally, we have statements from former classmates corroborating that ms. watson immediately told friends that mr. fairfax had raped her.” the letter adds that watson was “upset” after another woman, dr. vanessa tyson, came forward with her own accusations of sexual assault against fairfax earlier this week.

tyson claims fairfax sexually assaulted her at the democratic national convention in 2004, forcing her to perform oral sex in his hotel room. he has repeatedly denied the allegations.
.

breaking news
.

a second woman has come forward accusing virginia lieutet governor justin fairfax of sexual assault.

in a letter from her lawyer, meredith watson claims she was raped by fairfax in 2000, when they were both students at duke university. 
the letter characterizes the alleged attack as “premeditated and aggressive.” the two were friends but never dated or had any romantic relationship,” the letter says. “ms. watson shared her account of the rape with friends in a series of emails and facebook messages that are now in our possession,” the letter continues. “additionally, we have statements from former classmates corroborating that ms. watson immediately told friends that mr. fairfax had raped her.” the letter adds that watson was “upset” after another woman, dr. vanessa tyson, came forward with her own accusations of sexual assault against fairfax earlier this week.

tyson claims fairfax sexually assaulted her at the democratic national convention in 2004, forcing her to perform oral sex in his hotel room. he has repeatedly denied the allegations.

text:
thank you for wearing yellow today and for following / support victim support's sexual awareness #takeover of gef 💛

we could not be more in awe of paula gelling and the whole victim support iom team; a charity that does so much incredible work to support victims of all crimes, here on the isle of man 🇮🇲 if you'd like to learn more about the charity, or donate to their cause, head straight on over to the link in our bio, and hit this image to go direct to their website 👈

if you or someone you know has been a victim of sexual assault you can contact victim support on 679950 or enquiries@victimsupport.im or the victim support uk 24 hour helpline on 0808 168911 📞

victim support’s welfare team are specifically trained to support those affected by sexual crimes. the crime does not have to have been recent. they support many people where the crime occurred years ago. 🙅🙅‍♂️ #itsnotok

text:
the hardest thing i've been struggling my whole life is to let go of the past.

when i was younger i was raped and molested by my step father for 7 years. my childhood was taken from me. i had the mind set that, "my brother and sister have to be alright", i fed them, protected them. i made sure they never had to endure what i went through. after a neighbor had stumbled into his bedroom one morning and had saw me, a naked 11 year old sleeping in the bed with her stepfather who was in his underwear. 3 days later, i was moving to california to be with my mom... but he stayed behind, when i had the courage to say something to the police, less than a year and half later, the statue of limitations had gone into affect and there's nothing anyone can do. i have severe ptsd and i struggle more than anybody would understand just by looking at me.. i'm stronger than my past. i'm a person who will do anything for everyone me because i know what it's like to be alone. i know what it's like to hit rock bottom. i know what it's like to feel like bruised fruit. and to feel like your just damaged goods that no one could ever possibly love. but i also know you're wrong. you're relient. you're strength. you're the meaning of beauty in this world, because you are still here, proving that they didn't win..

text:
"gorda como insulto, puta como insulto, frígida como insulto, lesbiana como insulto, vieja como insulto, mujer como insulto. porque ellos saben que mi cuerpo no es mío. que, como el de todas las mujeres, es un campo de conquista, una fábrica de satisfacciones, un expendedor de cuidados.

porque ellos creen que todas estamos pendientes de su aprobación sobre nuestro aspecto físico, que todas estamos preocupadas por su opinión, que todas queremos gustarles, que todas deseamos ser penetradas por sus penes erectos, que todas les tenemos miedo.

y, cuando de repente aparece alguna que no les tiene miedo, que no busca ni su aprobación ni su respeto, ni le interesa lo que opinen de su cuerpo… se enfadan, se burlan, se abalanzan. pero, en el fondo, sólo sienten desconcierto. porque han vivido en un mundo que les ha dado privilegios, sin merecerlos. han crecido en un mundo en el que les han convencido que debían de cumplirse todos sus deseos. que las mujeres estamos ahí para admirarles, para escucharles, para gustarles, para esperarles, para mover la cabeza con aprobación mientras nos dan consejos, para cuidarles, para acompañarles, para darles otra oportunidad, para entenderles y empatizar con ellos, para convencerles, para reír sus chistes, para que nos follen, para poner el culo, para lamerles los huevos."
📍ilustración: @florpochi 📍texto: irantzu varela
